name: Amanda Kay Whiddon
text: Rehobeth is a quiet little town with  amazing schools.  They have a really big football program, a very nice stadium, and one of our favorite little parks where we can walk while the kids play safely.  Rehobeth is home to one of my favorite DG which is always super stocked and organized.  Rehobeth Baptist Church is a pillar in the community and has great activities for the kids.  Home of one of the areas best daycares, Little Rebels, who have been in the business for over 20...maybe 30 years!  New to Rehobeth is one of my newest favorite places to shop...TruValue!  When I say this place has a little bit of everything...I'm not lying!  Mixed with super friendly and helpful staff...this new home town addition is sure to put Rehobeth much bigger on the map.  My first trip there the salesman not only helped me locate what I was hunting but he went all out and downloaded the directions to make my French drain dreams come true!  Beautiful homes, Southern born and bread families...Rehobeth has it all!  But shhhh...don't tell everybody...I'm sure they like it just the way it is!

name: Preston Holloway
text: Lots of good times here. It is a beautiful sleepy little community. My friends and I broke up the serenity here for over a decade with dirt bikes, bottle rocked wars, and Bon fire parties. I am sorry for the people that put up with us, but it was the greatest way to grow up and experience life here. When I grew up I kept coming back. Sometimes I came to remember old memories and sometimes to make new ones. This place will always have a special place inside of me. Cheers you beautiful little pond. I have videos on YouTube of some of my exploits here if you are feeling brave.

name: Lesley Hall
text: Clean, well-kept, thoughtfully built and run.  The mega-large (2-3  acres?) pool with the slides meant for smaller children are on one level/side of the park, separated from larger attractions by buildings for concessions and bathrooms.  Picnic tables are everywhere, and for a small charge ($12) you can bring your vehicle right up poolside.  There are 6-7 bigger exciting attractions on the higher level. The lifeguards I saw didn't overpolice or enjoy being bossy, but they did pay attention to safety, which is how it should be. I appreciated the thoughtfulness of little water sprays on surfaces that would have gotten too hot for bare feet.  I only tried a bit of the food, as we had picnic food, but the ice cream cones were generous and the funnel cake and fried oreos were excellent!  My cousin gets a season pass every year and I see why.  I will be bringing my family back.
